  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Lodging at Buheung Temple
  author: Byeon Gyeyangn
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Lost on the path, I wandered into a mountain temple—
    people say this place is called Buheung.
    Among the green pines, only cranes are visible;
    even in broad daylight, no monks appear.
    On ancient walls, golden Buddhas linger;
    in empty rafters, jade lamps flicker with flame.
    The front veranda is pristine and clear—
    a lone traveler comes to rest against its rail.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Buheung Temple (復興寺): The name suggests ''restoration'' or ''revival,'' perhaps hinting at the temple''s abandoned or decaying state despite its name.'
